cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with the design of codes for distributed data storage networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of multiple racks also brings in the aspect of network infrastructure (cs.NI) and distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the use of linear programming to optimize the code rate brings in the aspect of control systems (cs.SY).
